Target: OntoElecPowerEquipment is an ontology for power electronic devices.

Comment: An object designed and manufactured to perform one or more functions.
Label: Power source

Comment: An object that manipulates certain variable of the power transmitted
Label: Power modifier

Comment: An object that analyses the properties of the power transmitted
Label: Power analyser

Comment: A power source that supplies electricity from power socket in a regulated manner
Label: Power supply

Comment: A power source that supplies electricity when the main power source is down
Label: Power back up

Comment: A power source that generates electricity through photoelectric effect.
Label: Solar cell system

Comment: A device that increase/decrease current or voltage using the principles of electromagnetism.
Label: Transformer

Comment: A transformer that manipulates the current in a circuit
Label: Current transformer

Comment: A device that increases the magnitude of power delivered through a transmission line
Label: PowerAmplifier

Comment: A device that increase the current on a power transmission line
Label: Current booster

Comment: A device that provides a real-time measurement of electrical quantities from across the power system.
Label: Microsynchrophasor

Comment: A device that monitors the parameters of a DC power transmission line
Label: DC power quality analyzer

Comment: A device that monitors the parameters of a AC power transmission line
Label: AC power quality analyzer
